30006171@@@@@@Title@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1576@LMC@2019-06-15
30006172@@@@@@Cam·Spec@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1577@LMC@2019-06-15
30006173@@@@@@Background@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1578@LMC@2019-06-15
30006174@@@@@@Photography emerged at the beginning of the 19th century.@@@@1@9@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1579@LMC@2019-06-15
30006175@@@@@@Since then, the number of pictures taken each year has increased exponentially, especially by the end of the 20th century [1].@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1580@LMC@2019-06-15
30006176@@@@@@Since year 2013, almost everybody has a mobile phone fitted with camera and due to that, there are 300 million photos uploaded to Facebook every day [2].@@@@1@27@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1581@LMC@2019-06-15
30006177@@@@@@Taking photo has become a habit of everyone.@@@@1@8@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1582@LMC@2019-06-15
30006178@@@@@@Problem@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1583@LMC@2019-06-15
30006179@@@@@@Now, using cameras to take pictures of the notes in lectures or tutorials is common practice.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1584@LMC@2019-06-15
30006180@@@@@@Apart from practical usage, some people use it to take pictures of scenery or interesting pictures.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1585@LMC@2019-06-15
30006181@@@@@@But, sometimes, the time we take to set up our mobile phone for or camera just lets slip the moments that we want to capture.@@@@1@25@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1586@LMC@2019-06-15
30006182@@@@@@Moreover, when cameras or mobile phones are out of battery, we are rendered unequipped to record moments.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1587@LMC@2019-06-15
30006183@@@@@@Actually Google designed Google Glass that is spectacles that can do many things include taking pictures.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1588@LMC@2019-06-15
30006184@@@@@@But in February 2015, Google Glass has been banned and redesigned until it become “perfect” [3].@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1589@LMC@2019-06-15
30006185@@@@@@This was because Google glass could identify strangers by MORIS (Mobile Offender Recognition and Identification System) [4].@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1590@LMC@2019-06-15
30006186@@@@@@So, the issue of privacy is once more brought up to the spotlight by its advocates.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1591@LMC@2019-06-15
30006187@@@@@@Solution@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:215; ntucle-sid:1592@LMC@2019-06-15
