30006222@@@@@@E-CONTROLLER@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1732@LMC@2019-06-15
30006223@@@@@@Background@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1733@LMC@2019-06-15
30006224@@@@@@Electricity is a crucial necessity which make our lives more convenient.@@@@1@11@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1734@LMC@2019-06-15
30006225@@@@@@However, power shortage has become a serious and urgent challenge of the modern society nowadays.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1735@LMC@2019-06-15
30006226@@@@@@On the one hand, the electricity consumption of the world is steadily growing over the years, according to the statistics from World Bank (2015) [1].@@@@1@25@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1736@LMC@2019-06-15
30006227@@@@@@On the other hand, the resources to fuel the power plants are depleting as oil, gas, and fuel are becoming scarce.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1737@LMC@2019-06-15
30006228@@@@@@Thus, it is each individual’s responsibility to save electricity.@@@@1@9@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1738@LMC@2019-06-15
30006229@@@@@@Problem@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1739@LMC@2019-06-15
30006230@@@@@@The most efficient way to save electricity is to switch off the unused domestic appliances.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1740@LMC@2019-06-15
30006231@@@@@@However, this action proves to be difficult for many people as they tend to forget to turn off the lights, fans, air conditioners, etc..., or it is their bad habit of leaving the appliances on.@@@@1@35@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1741@LMC@2019-06-15
30006232@@@@@@Although many electronic firms have included the “standby” function is their appliances to help minimizing this waste, it is reported that by turning off the appliances completely, such as unplugging them, one could save roughly 10% of the total electric bill[2].@@@@1@41@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1742@LMC@2019-06-15
30006233@@@@@@When taking into account billions of household in the world, such save is a big number.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1743@LMC@2019-06-15
30006234@@@@@@Solution@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1744@LMC@2019-06-15
30006235@@@@@@My device, E-Controller, is one of the best solutions to the problems mentioned above.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1745@LMC@2019-06-15
30006236@@@@@@E-Controller comprises of two parts: a central server and a remote control system.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1746@LMC@2019-06-15
30006237@@@@@@The central server will be integrated into the household circuit and will control and manage each appliance through a control panel, including disconnecting current, checking power consumption.@@@@1@27@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1747@LMC@2019-06-15
30006238@@@@@@The remote control system is a user-friendly mobile application on Android/iOS platform, enabling users to control the central server through the internet with their own phones.@@@@1@26@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1748@LMC@2019-06-15
30006239@@@@@@With these functions, users can manage appliances from everywhere.@@@@1@9@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1749@LMC@2019-06-15
30006240@@@@@@Benefits@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1750@LMC@2019-06-15
30006241@@@@@@Firstly, E-Controller can help users to manage the electricity usage and check whether there is an electricity leakage.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1751@LMC@2019-06-15
30006242@@@@@@Secondly, E-Controller can completely switch off any appliance without having to unplug it, thus easily cut down electricity losses because of standby mode.@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1752@LMC@2019-06-15
30006243@@@@@@Last but not least, the function of controlling through the internet allows “suddenly” forgetful users to turn off their air-conditioner at home, saving an enormous amount of electricity and money.@@@@1@30@ntucle-docid:216; ntucle-sid:1753@LMC@2019-06-15
