30006402@@@@@@LED indicator lights in F&B outlets@@@@1@6@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1821@LMC@2019-06-15
30006403@@@@@@With an undergraduate population of 23713 [1], NTU is a very bustling place to be in.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1822@LMC@2019-06-15
30006404@@@@@@Even more so during mealtimes.@@@@1@5@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1823@LMC@2019-06-15
30006405@@@@@@As such, many staff and students find it difficult to locate an empty table at the respective food and beverages outlets in NTU.@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1824@LMC@2019-06-15
30006406@@@@@@For example, the food and beverages cluster in the South Spine which includes Koufu and 1983 café accommodates a maximum of 1050 people [2].@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1825@LMC@2019-06-15
30006407@@@@@@This is but a small fraction of just the undergraduate population, keeping in mind that there is still the faculty, staff and graduate populations to take into account.@@@@1@28@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1826@LMC@2019-06-15
30006408@@@@@@Not only are there insufficient seats for everybody, the seats are not put to efficient use either.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1827@LMC@2019-06-15
30006409@@@@@@There are cases of a 2 people taking up a 4 seat table, rendering the last 2 seats unusable to other people.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1828@LMC@2019-06-15
30006410@@@@@@Or people leave their belongings at their seats to go order their food and others, thinking they have found an empty table make their way over to be disappointed.@@@@1@29@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1829@LMC@2019-06-15
30006411@@@@@@My solution to this problem is to adapt the overhead LED indicator lights commonly found in multi-storey carparks to improve the experience of dinners at the food and beverages outlets.@@@@1@30@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1830@LMC@2019-06-15
30006412@@@@@@Another possible benefit of this system is that it could also lead to an increase in social interaction.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1831@LMC@2019-06-15
30006413@@@@@@The overhead LED indicators in carparks work using sensors to check if the lot has a car parked in it.@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1832@LMC@2019-06-15
30006414@@@@@@A corresponding light is then displayed to indicate the status of the lot.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1833@LMC@2019-06-15
30006415@@@@@@Combined with a digital display at the entrance of the carpark, it informs users of both the availability of lots as well as their locations.@@@@1@25@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1834@LMC@2019-06-15
30006416@@@@@@This allows the users to make informed decisions and thus improves their experience.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1835@LMC@2019-06-15
30006417@@@@@@By adapting this system for use in food and beverage outlets like food courts we could improve the dining experience for diners too.@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1836@LMC@2019-06-15
30006418@@@@@@I propose that every table will have an overhead indicator (green, amber and red) to indicate the status of the table.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1837@LMC@2019-06-15
30006419@@@@@@This is controlled by whoever is sitting at the particular table by a set of corresponding buttons.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1838@LMC@2019-06-15
30006420@@@@@@Red means that the table is full or already taken and whoever is sitting there does not want to share their table with strangers.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1839@LMC@2019-06-15
30006421@@@@@@Amber means that the table is taken but the person sitting there is open to the idea of sharing their table with others.@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1840@LMC@2019-06-15
30006422@@@@@@Lastly, green is for fully empty tables.@@@@1@7@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1841@LMC@2019-06-15
30006423@@@@@@Furthermore, there will also be digital displays at the entrances to the eateries that inform potential customers of the number of seats available.@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1842@LMC@2019-06-15
30006424@@@@@@In case diners forget to change the indicator lights back to green when they leave, every half hour, sensors will check if the customer has indeed left the table.@@@@1@29@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1843@LMC@2019-06-15
30006425@@@@@@This solution will not only help customers find seats more efficiently, but encourage people to be more sociable and interact with strangers as well.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1844@LMC@2019-06-15
30006426@@@@@@This is can be applied to any food and beverage outlet to improve the dining experience of the customers.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:222; ntucle-sid:1845@LMC@2019-06-15
